    "question_text": "At the beginning of the course, you obtained a job as the IT project manager responsible for\ndeployment of a new electronic health record system (EHR) to replace the current one in use at\nVirginia Women’s Center (VWC).\nVWC’s goal for deploying an EHR is to achieve excellence in quality and safety of clinical care, while\nalso improving financial performance. In addition, VWC can get federal government financial\nbenefits under various federal incentive programs like MIPS Promoting Interoperability.\nAs the head of the deployment program, you report to the VWC Chief Information Officer (CIO)\nwith overall responsibility for success of the deployment. This success is fundamentally measured\nby successfully implementing the EHR on time and on budget while also achieving the goals\ndescribed above.\nWhile the overall program was described at a high level by VWC leadership, as the project manager\nyou have had to put together the details of the project. While you have been in your job (the period\nof this course), you have done a tremendous amount of work gathering information about VWC, its clinical\nand business workflow, and its requirements for an EHR. You defined the security and interoperability\nstrategies for the EHR program and developed a project plan and budget for the deployment project.\nNow you need to do a project review presentation to the VWC’s IT leadership team, consisting of the\nCIO and their staff. The goal of the presentation is to inform the team about the overall project including\nkey items such as:\n• Project goals\n• Team members\n• Developing clinical workflow to reflect the new EHR\n• EHR functional requirements and the plans to meet them\n• EHR technical infrastructure required to support the chosen EHR and plan to implement that\ninfrastructure\n• EHR interoperability requirements and the plans to meet them\n• The overall project plan\n• High-level project budget\n• Project risks\n• Other items you feel should be covered\nThe presentation should also cover critical success or failure criteria for the full EHR deployment\nproject.\n\nCourse Project Approach\nThe course project is a culmination of the course. You should build on and incorporate the\nhomework assignments as well as the other aspects of the course to provide a summary of the\nproject to deploy a new EHR system for VWC. In addition, you should point out critical success or\nfailure criteria for the EHR deployment project. One way to help you conceptualize this is to think\nof creating a project notebook with the various sections incorporating key components of the\nproject. The final presentation should outline these elements.\n\nPresentation\nYou will give an approximately 20-25 minute, 12-17 slide PowerPoint presentation covering your\nplan for the project. In addition, prior to your presentation, you should post the presentation in\nMicrosoft PowerPoint, Google Slide, or Adobe PDF format on the course site. You should NOT use\nother formats as it makes it difficult if not impossible for the facilitators and professor to see your\nwork.\n\nSeveral other notes about the presentation:\n• The business requirements are in the VWC case study\n• Focus on what are the requirements, key parts of the solutions and how the VWC team will work\nto meet the requirements\n• You don’t need to provide specific and detailed specifications for software, hardware, etc.\n• The presentation should be able to be read “stand-alone” for people who are not able to attend.\n• Diagrams, bullet points, etc. are all fine.\n• 12-17 slides are fine but provide enough depth to bring out the issues but not too much given the\ngoal of providing a high-level overview and the time you have to present.\n• Scheduling for the course project presentations will be handled separately so look for an\nannouncement about that.",
    "independent_from_previous": true
